VAT Documentation
In order to recover the VAT on our expenditure we must have evidence that we have
paid VAT. There are different requirements depending on the amount. For expenditure
less than £250.00 the receipt/invoice must show the following:
Name and address of supplier
Date of supply
VAT registration number of the supplier
Description of goods/services purchased
VAT charged amounts and total amount paid
If the amount is greater than £250 we need a full VAT invoice which, in addition to the above,
must also show:
Customer address/invoiced to must be Imperial College Union, Beit Quadrangle,
Prince Consort Road, London, SW7 2BB
Invoice number and date
For each good/service : unit price, quantity, VAT rate/code
Separate net, VAT and gross totals
Some companies do not produce VAT receipts automatically. If one is not provided
you should always request one.
